From the manufacturer

ABOUT LEE

Steeped in almost 130 years of history, heritage denim brand Lee is recognized as a founding father of the modern denim movement. One of the world first denim brands, it has never let its rich history weight it down and instead, imbued with the spirit of innovation coupled with respect for tradition, has continued to shape trends, taking workwear and spinning it into something altogether more fashion-forward and modern.

Lee Jeans is part of the FOR A WORLD THAT WORKS initiative

Introducing For A World That Works, an initiative that unites Lee Jeans' values and heritage with a vision for our planet's future to redefine how Lee operates. Lee will create a more sustainable future through purposeful design, meaningful partnerships and a commitment to our planet.

Product description

Jane is our ultimate mid-rise waist, straight leg fit. Crafted with a full length leg to add volume to your silhouette, there is extra room through the whole fit, from the slightly lowered waistband to the thigh, knee and to the ankle, making Jane a perfect blend of comfort and super-cool, contemporary cut. These are made using a nicely-weighted denim constructed using recycled cotton and a blend of stretch yarn for added movement and easy-wear. The mid-blue finish is iconic - note the extra depth of colour where the dye marbles on seams and plackets. This has been created using our low impact Indigood dye process. Shot through with Mid Western detailing, look out for the cowboy-styling of the twin chest pockets and the pointed yoke on the shoulder. Pockets and placket use snap fasteners. regular waist straight leg zip fly

How we keep reviews trustworthy

Our goal is to ensure that every review reflects an actual customer’s experience.

Before posting a review, we verify its authenticity by using advanced technology in combination with human investigators. This helps us stop fake reviews before customers ever see them.

We also check and stop reviews that violate our Community guidelines. We suspend Amazon accounts and take legal action against groups that pay others in exchange for reviews. Learn more
